{"questionId":"19214","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Interchanging <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> can be done at any stage.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mroot><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>3</mn></mroot><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mroot><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>3</mn></mroot><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mroot><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>3</mn></mroot><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;must be seen for the final <em><strong>A</strong></em> mark.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19214","referenceCode":"20N.1.AHL.TZ0.H_10b.iii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence find g-1(x).","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.13—Rational functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}